  • Cut 3-4 onion in small small pieces
  • Wash and cut 2 green chili horizontally in small small pieces
  • Take 2-3 leaf of garlic, clean and wash them nicely.
  • Take a very small piece of ginger.
  • Put ginger and garlic in mixer grinder and make a fine paste of it and side by side put green peas(100-200 gm) for boiling on gas stove.
  • Take 2-3 table spoon oil and put in a pan and switch the gas stove on.
  • Once the oil is heated, put the cumin seeds and wait until they turn brownish.
  • Add the paste of ginger garlic and fry it nicely in the oil, until the oil comes at the surface.
  • Put chopped green chili in pan to fry and after few seconds put the chopped onions as well.
  • until the onion turn golden brown, mash the farmer's cheese (200 gm) nicely and make it powder type.
  • Once the onion is turned golden brown, put the remaining spices, like red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder almost 1 tbsp each.
  • Add salt as per taste.
  • Mix the spices nicely and add the boiled green peas in it.
  • Add the farmer's cheese powder into it and mix it well.
  • Wait for 5-7 min and the Recipe is done. You can close the gas stove and serve it with chapatis or bread.
